catalog_description:
• Please do not attend this reservation if you are experiencing flu-like symptoms, travelled outside of the province in the last 14 days, or have been in contact with anyone confirmed to be infected with Covid -19. The onsite supervisor has the right to allow or prevent access to any part of the pool or the pool in its entirety should there be any safety concerns regarding the patron’s use of the facility.
  • This public swim reservation will grant you access to the shallow end; after successfully completing a swim test, access to the deep end (diving boards) may be granted (space permitting).
  • Mid-section lap swim and gym space is also reservable (space permitting); due to social distancing parameters, access to these additional areas cannot be guaranteed without a reservation
  • Please arrive dressed to swim; access to showers, lockers, washrooms will be reduced and cleaned frequently, as will public spaces
  • Please maintain a 2 metre (6 feet) separation between staff and patrons whenever possible; limit close encounters to less than 10 minutes (not applicable to people living together in the same household)
  • All public admission height requirements are to be adhered to
  • A limited number of lifejackets and Personal Floatation Devices (PFDs) will be available for public use; please bring your own lifejacket or PFD if possible
  • Toys (i.e. balls) will not be made available for public use; please bring your own toys (use is at discretion of the lifeguard)
  • Water fountains are restricted to bottle filling only
  • The dive tank (diving boards) is not accessible from 6:30-7:30pm
online_notes:
Precautions
  • You are reminded to exercise precautions to protect against the spread of illness
  • Everyone should practice good handwashing hygiene and wash your hands with soap and warm water for at least 20 seconds and dry them thoroughly—if you are unable to wash your hands, use an alcohol-based hand cleanser
  • Cover your mouth and nose with a tissue when coughing or sneezing, or cough or sneeze into your sleeve—throw used tissues in the garbage and immediately wash your hands, or use an alcohol-based hand cleanser
  • Avoid touching your eyes, nose, and mouth
  • Minimize prolonged (more than 10 minutes), close (less than two meters/six feet) contact with individuals in public
  • Avoid travel, crowded places and events, especially if you are at higher risk(e.g. seniors and those with underlying medical conditions)
  • If you are unwell, stay at home

catalog_description:
Ce cours est combiné: Croix-Rouge Natation junior niveau 9 et Croix-Rouge Natation junior niveau 10. Les participants de niveau 9 et niveau 10 peuvent s'y inscrire. Veuillez informer votre moniteur/monitrice du niveau de compétence de votre enfant dès le début des leçons.

Niveau 9

Dans ce niveau, les nageurs et les nageuses perfectionnent leurs techniques de crawl, de dos crawlé, de dos élémentaire et de brasse. Ils s'habitueront a nager pour garder la forme. Ils travailleront également le plongeon à la surface, le plongeon debout en eau peu profonde, le coup de pied de marinière et les choix judicieux, ainsi que les techniques de sauvetage, concernant la sécurité sur la glace. Les enfants developperont leur endurance en nageant une distance de 400m.
Ce cours s'adresse aux enfants de 6 ans ou plus. Les participants doivent avoir cet âge le jour du début des leçons.
Prérequis: Croix-Rouge Natation junior, niveau 8 ou l'équivalent.
Niveau suivant: Croix-Rouge Natation junior, niveau 10.

Niveau 10

Les nageurs et les nageuses continuent de perfectionner leurs nages. À ce niveau, les enfants s'initient à la marinière. Les renseignements sur la sécurité nautique fournis portent sur la prudence au soleil et le sauvetage sur glace. Les enfants développent leur endurance en nageant sur une distance de 500 mètres et en pratiquant les battements dauphin verticaux.
Ce cours s'adresse aux enfants de 6 ans ou plus. Les participants doivent avoir cet âge le jour du début des leçons.
Prérequis: Croix-Rouge Natation junior, niveau 9 ou l'équivalent.
Niveau suivant: (si le nageur ou la nageuse est plus jeune que 13 ans) (si le nageur ou la nageuse a 13 ans avant la date de la dernière leçon de Médaille de bronze). Les cours de sauvetage ne sont enseignés qu'en anglais.
online_notes:
Ce cours est combiné: Croix-Rouge Natation junior niveau 9 et Croix-Rouge Natation junior niveau 10. Les participants de niveau 9 et niveau 10 peuvent s'y inscrire. Veuillez informer votre moniteur/monitrice du niveau de compétence de votre enfant dès le début des leçons.

Niveau 9

Prérequis: Croix-Rouge Natation junior, niveau 8 ou l'équivalent.

catalog_description:
Bronze Medallion teaches lifesaving principles, incorporating the four components of water rescue education: judgement, knowledge, skill and fitness. Participants learn tows, carries and release methods in preparation for challenging rescues of increased risk. They also learn to respond to increasingly complex situations, involving conscious and unconscious victims, in contact and non-contact rescues. Endurance swim of 500 meters in 15 minutes is required for successful completion of this level. Successful participants receive the Bronze Medallion and Lifesaving CPR B awards. 100% attendance and participation is recommended. Prerequisites: Bronze Star by the first day of the course or 13 years of age by the date of the exam.

Next Level: Lifesaving - Bronze Cross
online_notes:
Participants are required to purchase the following non-refundable items (available at the pool)

*The Canadian Lifesaving Manual approximate cost $43.00 *A Leadership Starter Kit (gloves, whistle, mouth barrier) approximate cost $12.00

catalog_description:
This is a combined course: Red Cross Swim Crocodile and Red Cross Swim Whale. Participants in Crocodile and Whale may register in this course. Please inform the instructor at the first class what level your child is working on.

Crocodile
Youngsters get more adventurous in Crocodile, as they start independent glides and kicking in deep water. Endurance is built through increasing distance for front and back swims. Swimmers will continue working on side glides and demonstrating a distance swim of 10 meters.
Designed for children 3 - 5 years of age. Participants must be minimum age by course start date.
Prerequisite: Red Cross Swim - Sunfish or equivalent.

Whale
Independent preschoolers will have a 'whale' of a time! Preschoolers will increase their swimming distance to 15 meters, improve skills in front and back swims and be introduced to sitting dives. Swimmers also learn about throwing assists to help another person in the water.
Designed for children 3 - 5 years of age. Participants must be minimum age by course start date.
Prerequisite: Red Cross Swim - Crocodile or equivalent.

activity_name: Red Cross Blended - Standard First Aid & CPR C/AED
catalog_description:
This course is recommended for individuals with prior Standard First Aid certification.

The course will provide registrants with the knowledge to respond to emergencies in the home, community or workplace. A variety of topics are covered: how to access the EMS system; recognize and respond to airway, breathing and cardiovascular emergencies; bone, muscle, joint, head and spinal injuries; bleeding and shock; first aid for poisonings; environmental emergencies; and CPR/AED.

Blended Learning: combines online learning and in-person skills session. Registration cut off is one week prior to the in class date. Candidates must have a valid email address to register. This comprehensive 16 hour course is comprised of an 8 hour online study session and an 8 hour in class skills evaluation session. The online portion of this program must be completed before the in class portion.
online_notes:
* 100 % attendance and participation are required.

* Email required to access the online content.

*Online content must be completed prior to the first in class day.

Participants are asked to wear comfortable clothing to the course. All required texts and course materials are included in course fee. No refunds after online access granted. Awards are issued to the candidate electronically through email. Certification of this award is for 3 years.

A one hour lunch break is included for the in class session.

activity_name: Red Cross - Water Safety Instructor Course
catalog_description:
The Water Safety Instructor (WSI) course prepares candidates to instruct Red Cross Swim programs.

Pre-Course Requirements:

15 years or older by the last day of the WSI course, ability to perform Red Cross Swim Kids Level 10 strokes and skills, and hold one of the following certifications (not required to be current):

Bronze Cross, Red Cross Assistant Lifeguard, or Emergency First Aid.

Candidates must attend, participate, and complete 100% of all four course components.

All course components are evaluated against specific evaluation criteria on a pass/fail basis

All course manuals are included in the course fee.

Course Components & Length:

Skills Evaluation: 6 hours

Online Component: 2 weeks

Teaching Experience : minimum
online_notes:
The first day is a 6 hour Pre Screening assessment. Once successful, the candidates will receive their manuals and course information.

*Refunds will only be applicable after the Pre Screening. Once the manuals are given out, and the online component started, refunds will not be processed.*

*Please have open availability for the middle weeks of the course, as this is for the Practice Teaching component.*

All course manuals are included in the course fee.

Classes are on Saturday Sept 15 and Mondays, Practice teaching runs 3 weeks. Please maintain open availability during those 3 weeks.

catalog_description: Course consists of warm-up, cardio portion and then a cool down to work on strength and resistance. An easy way to get a real workout and minimize risk of injury!

Bronze Cross is designed for lifesavers who want the challenge of more advanced training. Bronze Cross teaches the difference between lifesaving and lifeguarding, the principles of emergency procedures and teamwork. Lifesavers learn the skills involved in the rescue of a victim with a spinal injury, the rescue of a pulseless victim and the rescue of a victim with deteriorating circumstances. Endurance swim of 600 meters in 18 minutes is required for successful completion of this level. Successful participants receive the Bronze Cross and Lifesaving CPR C awards. 100 % attendance and participation is recommended. Participants must provide Bronze Medallion card to the instructor at the first class. Prerequisites: Bronze Medallion Next Lifesaving Level: Distinction or at 16 years of age: Lifesaving - National Lifeguard Service Award (NLS) or Lifesaving & First Aid Instructor Course

catalog_description:
National Lifeguard certification is Canada's professional lifeguard standard. This training develops a sound understanding of lifeguarding principles, good judgement, and a mature and responsible attitude towards the lifeguards role. It emphasizes prevention and effective rescue response in emergencies including first aid treatment. Candidates develop teamwork, leadership and communication skills. Fitness requirements include a timed object recovery, 50 meter sprint challenge, 50 meter rescue drill and 400 meter endurance challenge. Program includes classroom and water activities. 100 % attendance and participation are required. Prerequisites: 16 years age, Bronze Cross and Standard First Aid

This training develops a sound understanding of lifeguarding principles, good judgement, and a mature and responsible attitude towards the lifeguards role. It emphasizes prevention and effective rescue response in emergencies including first aid treatment. Candidates develop teamwork, leadership and communication skills. Fitness requirements include a timed object recovery, 50 meter sprint challenge, 50 meter rescue drill and 400 meter endurance challenge. Program includes classroom and water activities.  100 % attendance and participation are required.  Prerequisites: 16 years age, Bronze Cross and Standard First Aid
online_notes:
Participants must give prerequisites to the instructor at the first class * 16 years of age * Bronze Cross * Standard First Aid award Participants are required to purchase the following non-refundable items (available at the pool): * Canadian Lifesaving Manual - approximate cost $43.00 * Alert, Lifeguarding in Action - approximate cost $43.00 * National Lifeguard Award Guide - approximate cost $24.00 * a Leadership Starter Kit (gloves, whistle, mouth barrier) - approximate cost $12.00 * Program includes classroom and water activities - 100% attendance and participation is required * Fitness requirements include a timed object recovery, 50 meter sprint challenge, 50 meter rescue drill and 400 meter endurance challenge. * NLS Awards will be mailed to successful candidates by the Lifesaving Society

catalog_description: Welcome to the City of Winnipeg's premiere children's road safety program! Operating June 7 - August 4, Cartown is designed to teach children about driving safety in an entertaining, realistic town setting. Each session includes games and songs, pedestrian safety and road instruction. A driver's license is issued at the end of each session. For safety reason participants must meet the following requirements: Weight maximum is 70 lbs (31.2 kg) and ages 4-7 years. Parents ... we encourage your assistance with the program to ensure maximum enjoyment. Pre-registration is recommended by calling 311. Same day registration is accepted on site, subject to availability (exact payment in cash or credit card only).
online_notes: No age overrides - Participants under the age of 4 are allowed to participate in the program as a passengers in the vehicles that have passenger seats or play on the play structure in the Cartown town.

catalog_description:
Calling all adventurous, fun-seekers to come join us for some "summer fun in the sun", make new friends and enjoy an action packed week of activities and games, led by qualified staff in a safe environment. We will make "messes & masterpieces" when we get creative with crafts. We will enjoy some "lip-smacking snacks" and "incredible edibles" when we put our chef hats on. "Sing & dance" our way through the week as we "move & groove" to our favourite music and songs. We will also "explore & discover" as we trek-out on some "urban adventures" and outings in the surrounding neighbourhood and local area. Are you excited and curious about the activities that we have in store for you; then "come on down" and check-out "WHAT'S UP!"

Program Highlights: For ages (6-12); crafts, games, sports, music, cooking & gardening activities & outings.

catalog_description: Spend quality time with your child while you both have fun, learn and socialize Through structured in water interaction between parent and child, we stress the importance of play in developing water positive attitudes. This program is participation based, without formal evaluation. Non-toilet trained infants/toddlers must wear leak-proof swim pants or garments of a similar nature. Participants must be minimum age by course start date. Next Level: Red Cross Swim - Sea Otter when child is 3 years of age

catalog_description:
Ce cours est combiné: Croix-Rouge Natation junior niveau 7 et Croix-Rouge Natation junior niveau 8. Les participants de niveau 7 et niveau 8 peuvent s'y inscrire. Veuillez informer votre moniteur/monitrice du niveau de compétence de votre enfant dès le début des leçons.

Niveau 7

Dans ce niveau, les nageurs utilisent et perfectionnent leurs techniques de crawl, de dos crawlé et de dos élémentaire. Introduction au coup de pied fouetté sur le ventre. On apprend aux enfants ce qu'est l'obstruction des voies respiratoires. Ils développeront leur endurance en nageant une distance de 150 mètres.
Ce cours s'adresse aux enfants de 6 ans ou plus. Les participants doivent avoir cet âge le jour du début des leçons.
Prérequis: Croix-Rouge Natation junior, niveau 6 ou l'équivalent.
Niveau suivant: Croix-Rouge Natation junior, niveau 8

Niveau 8

Dans ce niveau, les enfants apprennent la brasse, le plongeon de surface, le saut d'arrêt et le rétropédalage. On enseigne aux enfants les dangers de l'eau libre et de l'hypothermie ainsi que le bouche à bouche sur les enfants et sur les adultes. Les enfants développeront leur endurance en nageant une distance de 300 mètres.
Ce cours s'adresse aux enfants de 6 ans ou plus. Les participants doivent avoir cet âge le jour du début des leçons.
Prérequis: Croix-Rouge Natation junior, niveau 7 ou l'équivalent.
Niveau suivant: Croix-Rouge Natation junior, niveau 9.

catalog_description:
Ce cours est combiné: Croix-Rouge Natation junior niveau 7 et Croix-Rouge Natation junior niveau 8. Les participants de niveau 7 et niveau 8 peuvent s'y inscrire. Veuillez informer votre moniteur/monitrice du niveau de compétence de votre enfant dès le début des leçons.

Niveau 7

Dans ce niveau, les nageurs utilisent et perfectionnent leurs techniques de crawl, de dos crawlé et de dos élémentaire. Introduction au coup de pied fouetté sur le ventre. On apprend aux enfants ce qu'est l'obstruction des voies respiratoires. Ils développeront leur endurance en nageant une distance de 150 mètres.
Ce cours s'adresse aux enfants de 6 ans ou plus. Les participants doivent avoir cet âge le jour du début des leçons.
Prérequis: Croix-Rouge Natation junior, niveau 6 ou l'équivalent.
Niveau suivant: Croix-Rouge Natation junior, niveau 8

Niveau 8

Dans ce niveau, les enfants apprennent la brasse, le plongeon de surface, le saut d'arrêt et le rétropédalage. On enseigne aux enfants les dangers de l'eau libre et de l'hypothermie ainsi que le bouche à bouche sur les enfants et sur les adultes. Les enfants développeront leur endurance en nageant une distance de 300 mètres.
Ce cours s'adresse aux enfants de 6 ans ou plus. Les participants doivent avoir cet âge le jour du début des leçons.
Prérequis: Croix-Rouge Natation junior, niveau 7 ou l'équivalent.
Niveau suivant: Croix-Rouge Natation junior, niveau 9.

Calling all adventurous, fun-seekers to come join us for some "summer fun in the sun", make new friends and enjoy an action packed week of activities and games, led by qualified staff in a safe environment. We will make "messes & masterpieces" when we get creative with crafts. We will enjoy some "lip-smacking snacks" and "incredible edibles" when we put our chef hats on. "Sing & dance" our way through the week as we "move & groove" to our favourite music and songs. We will also "explore & discover" as we trek-out on some "urban adventures" and outings in the surrounding neighbourhood and local area. Are you excited and curious about the activities that we have in store for you; then "come on down" and check-out "WHAT'S UP!"

catalog_description:
The Aquatic Emergency Response Training and Evaluation Course is a two module program that is a condition of employment for all City of Winnipeg Instructor/Guards. 100 % attendance, participation and successful completion are required. Only current City of Winnipeg Instructor Guard employees are eligible to register for this program.

This is a Lifeguard shift; employees are paid to attend.

Course transfers or withdrawals are only permitted in compliance with the Lifeguard time off procedure and can only be processed with approval in writing from the Pool Supervisor of the employee's home cluster.

Front desk staff processing transfer/withdrawal must email the written approval from the Pool Supervisor to cms-aquaticservicesdivisionreporting@winnipeg.ca.

100% course attendance and participation are required. Courses start on time - latecomers will not be admitted 10 minutes into the course.

Candidates must be prepared to participate in all activities.

This course is for students who have completed the beginner class. It builds upon the basic principles of Karate that turn movements into viable techniques. Also included is an expanded repertoire of movements, basic kata and basic partner training.
online_notes:
No class on Jan 25 and Feb 15. The last class will be March 21 rather than March 14.

Instructor is qualified with the Japan Karate Association. Uniforms and belts for testing can be ordered through the instructor for an additional cost and is optional.

catalog_description: Bronze Medallion teaches lifesaving principles, incorporating the four components of water rescue education: judgement, knowledge, skill and fitness. Participants learn tows, carries and release methods in preparation for challenging rescues of increased risk. They also learn to respond to increasingly complex situations, involving conscious and unconscious victims, in contact and non-contact rescues. Endurance swim of 500 meters in 15 minutes is required for successful completion of this level. Successful participants receive the Bronze Medallion and Lifesaving CPR B awards. 100 % attendance and participation is recommended. Prerequisites: Bronze Star by the first day of the course or 13 years of age by the date of the exam Next Level: Lifesaving - Bronze Cross

online_notes:
Prerequisite: must have completed Sunfish or equivalent.

*This activity is combined with Whale #19913

Please practice healthy swimming behaviours:

*Please do not go swimming if you are feeling unwell, especially if you have an upset stomach

*Please do not bring your child to swimming lessons if they are feeling unwell, have diarrhea, are vomiting (or have vomited in the past day) or have a cough

*Non-toilet trained participants must wear leak-proof swim pants or garments of a similar nature

*Avoid swallowing the pool water or getting water in your mouth

*Please do not feed your child before swimming and do not go swimming for one hour after eating

In the event that our pool water is contaminated with fecal matter or vomit, facility staff are required to close the pool for 2 - 24 hours in order to properly disinfect the water and ensure water quality is within the appropriate range set by the public health act before swimmers can re-enter the pool.

Thank you for your co-operation!

catalog_description:
Red Cross Swim - People with Disabilities lessons are available for individuals with developmental, cognitive and/or physical disabilities. These classes focus on developing sound water safety skills. They are designed to follow the Red Cross Swim program and provide an opportunity for supervised water activities.

These classes are for people with disabilities only.

When the participant and their caregiver meet the instructor on the first day of the program, the instructor will take appropriate steps to ensure instruction is tailored to the participant's needs.

activity_name: Red Cross - Water Safety Instructor Course
catalog_description:
The Water Safety Instructor (WSI) course prepares candidates to instruct Red Cross Swim programs.

Pre-Course Requirements:

15 years or older by the last day of the WSI course, ability to perform Red Cross Swim Kids Level 10 strokes and skills, and hold one of the following certifications (not required to be current):

Bronze Cross, Red Cross Assistant Lifeguard, or Emergency First Aid.

Candidates must attend, participate, and complete 100% of all four course components.

All course components are evaluated against specific evaluation criteria on a pass/fail basis

All course manuals are included in the course fee.

Course Components & Length:

Skills Evaluation: 6 hours

Online Component: 2 weeks

Teaching Experience : minimum
online_notes:
The first day is a 6 hour Pre Screening assessment. Once successful, the candidates will receive their manuals and course information.

*Refunds will only be applicable after the Pre Screening. Once the manuals are given out, and the online component started, refunds will not be processed.*

*Please have open availability for the middle weeks of the course, as this is for the Practice Teaching component. *

All course manuals are included in the course fee.

activity_name: Red Cross Swim - People with Disabilities
catalog_description:

catalog_description: This 4 hour course/exam will review/examine  the June 2012 revised NLS Pool course (NLS Core and Pool). Participants must give the examiner the prerequisites before the course starts.  Prerequisites are NLS Pool  (or NLS Core and Pool). All participants must bring an Updated Alert Manual with the Alert Insert featuring the new or newly emphasized technical content. The Alert Insert is available without charge by visiting the Lifesaving Manitoba web site to print the required document. (http://lifesaving.mb.ca/files/98AlertInsert_PRINT.pdf) All participants must also bring  a Leadership Starter Kit (gloves, whistle, and mouth shield).  Candidates should review the Alert Insert, make yourself familiar with the revised requirements which include a fitness component, and prepare to be evaluated on the mandatory recertification items.                  Program includes classroom and water activities, 100% attendance and participation is required.
online_notes:

Parent/caregiver must accompany the child in the water until the instructor indicates otherwise. We will help them jump into shallow water. activity_name: Red Cross Swim - People with Disabilities
catalog_description:
Red Cross Swim - People with Disabilities lessons are available for individuals with developmental, cognitive and/or physical disabilities. These classes focus on developing sound water safety skills. They are designed to follow the Red Cross Swim program and provide an opportunity for supervised water activities.

These classes are for people with disabilities only.

When the participant and their caregiver meet the instructor on the first day of the program, the instructor will take appropriate steps to ensure instruction is tailored to the participant's needs.

activity_name: Masalas: The Secret Behind Indian Cooking
catalog_description:
Masalas are the quintessential ingredient for so many Indian meals. It requires you to artfully smell, blend, roast and mix spices, herbs and different fruits in perfect proportions. Take home all the samples you make during the class. All ingredients are included. Class will end with a taste testing.

Lab fee: $25.00 cash payable to the instructor.
online_notes:
Lab fee: $25.00 cash payable to the instructor.

Participants can bring their own teacups and containers to take some herbs and spices home.

For courses conducted on a three day or less basis, no account credit will be given after 7 days prior to the course start date.

catalog_description:
Semi-private swim lessons have only two students per instructor. Instruction will be customized to provide opportunities for candidates to participate in Red Cross programs or to improve specific strokes or skills.

For safety reasons, and to ensure this is a successful class, this class is designated for beginning swimmers age 6 -12 years who are in Red Cross Swim Kids Levels 1-3; it will be held primarily in the shallow end of the pool.

Participants must be minimum age by course start date.
online_notes:

activity_name: Red Cross Swim Kids Level 5 / Level 6
catalog_description:
This is a combined course: Red Cross Swim Kids Level 5 and Red Cross Swim Kids Level 6. Participants in Level 5 and Level 6 may register in this course. Please inform the instructor at the first class what level your child is working on.

Level 5

Swimmers are introduced to back crawl, sculling skills and whip kick on their back. Children learn stride dives and receive an introduction to safe boating skills. Endurance is built through a 50 meter swim.
Designed for children 6 years of age and older. Participants must be minimum age by course start date.
Prerequisite: Red Cross Swim Kids - Level 4 or equivalency
Next Level: Red Cross Swim Kids - Level 6

Level 6

Swimmers will refine their technique in front and back crawl. Children are introduced to elementary backstroke, dolphin kick, ice safety, rescue of others with throwing assists and the front dive. Endurance is built through a 75 meter swim.
Designed for children 6 years of age and older. Participants must be minimum age by course start date.
Prerequisite: Red Cross Swim Kids - Level 5 or equivalency
Next Level: Red Cross Swim Kids - Level 7
online_notes:
This is a combined course: Red Cross Swim Kids Level 5 and Red Cross Swim Kids Level 6. Participants in Level 5 and Level 6 may register in this course. Please inform the instructor at the first class what level your child is working on.

Level 5

Level 6

Prerequisite: Red Cross Swim Kids - Level 5 or equivalency

Next Level: Red Cross Swim Kids - Level 7

Prerequisite: Red Cross Swim - Sunfish or Red Cross Swim Kids - Level 1 or equivalency

catalog_description:
Calling all adventurous, fun-seekers to come join us for some "summer fun in the sun", make new friends and enjoy an action packed week of activities and games, led by qualified staff in a safe environment. We will make "messes & masterpieces" when we get creative with crafts. We will enjoy some "lip-smacking snacks" and "incredible edibles" when we put our chef hats on. "Sing & dance" our way through the week as we "move & groove" to our favourite music and songs. We will also "explore & discover" as we trek-out on some "urban adventures" and outings in the surrounding neighbourhood and local area. Are you excited and curious about the activities that we have in store for you; then "come on down" and check-out "WHAT'S UP!"

Program Highlights: For ages (6-12); crafts, games, sports, music, cooking & gardening activities & outings.
online_notes:
Please provide the instructor with a completed Participant Medical Information Form at the first class; you may fill it out prior to the class or in person. (This form will be mailed to you a week before each week starts). PLEASE ALERT the instructor of any allergies your child may have.

TIMES:

  • DROP-OFF: between 7:45-9:00am
  • STRUCTURED PROGRAMMING: 9:00am-4:00pm
  • PICK-UP: between 4:00-5:00pm SHARP! (Note: An extra fee may apply if you continue to pick your child up late; past 5:00pm).
  • (Children are supervised in unstructured free play during drop-off & pick-up time frames).

PLEASE BRING THE FOLLOWING DAILY:

  • A NUT-FREE bag lunch, drinking water, a drink & some snacks
  • Sunscreen, hat & bug-repellent
  • Swimsuit & towel (for water activities - Note: When a site is near a pool, this does not ensure that we will go swimming; we have strict staff ratios to follow and may not have extra staff to assist).
  • Wear comfortable clothing & shoes (appropriate for the weather and for games & crafts).

NOTE: All activities and locations may be subject to change. Additional minimal fees may apply.

activity_name: L'il Critters - Astronauts and Community Helpers
catalog_description:
L'il Astronauts:

Preschoolers, prepare for take-off as you explore outer space! Learn about planets, stars, astronauts and spaceships. Enjoy a week of traveling through space with a variety of crafts, games and songs.

L'il Community Helpers:

They're the people that you meet when you're walking down the street. This week we will discover what the people in our neighborhood do to make a difference.
online_notes:
AM DROP-OFF TIME: 9:00 - 9:15 AM

PM PICK UP TIME: 3:45 - 4:00 PM

All parents/guardians are required to fill out a medical form for participants including a medical health services number at the first class. Please alert the instructor to any allergies your child may have.

Children must be FULLY Potty trained (no Pull ups)and be able to function in the washroom independently. Children need to be the minimum of 3 years of age at the start of the program.

Parental participation is welcome but not required. Please dress your child appropriately for the weather. Please bring a hat, runners, bottle water, a nut free Lunch and snacks every day.

**NO PEANUTS OR NUT PRODUCTS ARE ALLOWED AT ANY CITY OF WINNIPEG CHILDREN'S PROGRAMS.**

category: ZZ - Staff Training - Internal Use Only
catalog_description:
The Aquatic Emergency Response Training and Evaluation Course is a two module program that is a condition of employment for all City of Winnipeg Instructor/Guards. 100 % attendance, participation and successful completion are required. Only current City of Winnipeg Instructor Guard employees are eligible to register for this program.

This is a Lifeguard shift; employees are paid to attend.

Course transfers or withdrawals are only permitted in compliance with the Lifeguard time off procedure and can only be processed with approval in writing from the Pool Supervisor of the employee's home cluster.

Front desk staff processing transfer/withdrawal must email the written approval from the Pool Supervisor to cms-aquaticservicesdivisionreporting@winnipeg.ca.

100% course attendance and participation are required. Courses start on time - latecomers will not be admitted 10 minutes into the course.

Candidates must be prepared to participate in all activities.

catalog_description: Welcome to the City of Winnipeg's premiere children's road safety program! Operating June 7 - August 4, Cartown is designed to teach children about driving safety in an entertaining, realistic town setting. Each session includes games and songs, pedestrian safety and road instruction. A driver's license is issued at the end of each session. For safety reason participants must meet the following requirements: Weight maximum is 70 lbs (31.2 kg) and ages 4-7 years. Parents ... we encourage your assistance with the program to ensure maximum enjoyment. Pre-registration is recommended by calling 311. Same day registration is accepted on site, subject to availability (exact payment in cash or credit card only).
online_notes: No age overrides - Participants under the age of 4 are allowed to participate in the program as a passengers in the vehicles that have passenger seats or play on the play structure in the Cartown town.

activity_name: Hula Hooping for Fitness & Play 9-12 years
catalog_description: Hula Hooping is more than spinning a circle around your waist.  Through games and activities you will master waist hooping and explore hand movements.  From there you will learn transitions to enable you to seamlessly change movements.  Hooping improves balance and coordination, promotes self confidence, lifts mood and sharpens the mind and reflexes.
online_notes: This class is 100% Child Fitness Tax Credit applicable. No class Feb 15.

category: ZZ - Staff Training - Internal Use Only
catalog_description:
This is a site specific orientation to familiarize the employee with new CO-VID 19 protocols, safety equipment and practices in the workplace.

Additionally site specific spinals will take place during this time, not limited to FLUME, Zero Grade and High Ledge. AER Spinal videos are listed on the AER Website https://www.winnipeg.ca/cms/aertraining/

Only current City of Winnipeg Instructor Guard employees are eligible to register for this program.

This is a Lifeguard shift; employees are paid to attend.

Course transfers or withdrawals are only permitted in compliance with the Lifeguard time off procedure and can only be processed with approval in writing from the Pool Supervisor of the employee's home cluster.

Front desk staff processing transfer/withdrawal must email the written approval from the Pool Supervisor to cms-aquaticservicesdivisionreporting@winnipeg.ca.

100% course attendance and participation are required. Courses start on time - latecomers will not be admitted 10 minutes into the course.

Candidates must be prepared to participate in all activities.

Please bring a bathing suit, towel and appropriate PPE.

Swimmers refine front crawl, back crawl, elementary backstroke, breaststroke and work towards swimming for fitness. They also work on head first surface dives, standing shallow dives, sidestroke kick and learn about wise choices, peer influences and self-rescue from ice. catalog_description:
À ce niveau pour débutants, les enfants s'initient aux rudiments de la nage. Le programme permet aux enfants de se familiariser avec l'eau. Ils prennent confiance et se sentent à l'aise en sautant dans une eau peu profonde et en s'initiant aux flotteurs, aux glissades et aux battements. Les enfants développent leur endurance en nageant sur une distance de 5 mètres.

Ce cours s'adresse aux enfants de 6 ans ou plus qui commencent à apprendre la natation.

Niveau suivant: Croix-Rouge Natation junior, niveau 2 ou niveau 2 Premium.

catalog_description: Welcome to the City of Winnipeg's premiere children's road safety program! Operating June 7 - August 4, Cartown is designed to teach children about driving safety in an entertaining, realistic town setting. Each session includes games and songs, pedestrian safety and road instruction. A driver's license is issued at the end of each session. For safety reason participants must meet the following requirements: Weight maximum is 70 lbs (31.2 kg) and ages 4-7 years. Parents ... we encourage your assistance with the program to ensure maximum enjoyment. Pre-registration is recommended by calling 311. Same day registration is accepted on site, subject to availability (exact payment in cash or credit card only).
online_notes: No age overrides - Participants under the age of 4 are allowed to participate in the program as a passengers in the vehicles that have passenger seats or play on the play structure in the Cartown town.

Precautions
  • You are reminded to exercise precautions to protect against the spread of illness
  • Everyone should practice good handwashing hygiene and wash your hands with soap and warm water for at least 20 seconds and dry them thoroughly—if you are unable to wash your hands, use an alcohol-based hand cleanser
  • Cover your mouth and nose with a tissue when coughing or sneezing, or cough or sneeze into your sleeve—throw used tissues in the garbage and immediately wash your hands, or use an alcohol-based hand cleanser

catalog_description: Spend quality time with your child while you both have fun, learn and socialize. Through structured in water interaction between parent and child, we stress the importance of play in developing water positive attitudes. The goal of this class is to experience buoyancy, movement and safe water entries. Designed for children 6 - 36 months, participating with a parent or caregiver. This program is participation based, without formal evaluation.Non-toilet trained infants/toddlers must wear leak-proof swim pants or garments of a similar nature.Participants must be minimum age by course start date.
